<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="221" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="31.[160,1156,521,651]" box="[160,276,521,547]" pageId="31" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,276,521,547]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="221">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[160,1156,521,651]" pageId="31" pageNumber="221">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Costa &amp; Duarte &amp; Iannuzzi &amp; Grossi" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Dupuis" baseAuthorityYear="2019" box="[160,396,556,581]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Tetragus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="221" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="impunctatus">
<emphasis box="[160,396,556,581]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="221">Tetragus impunctatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Costa &amp; Duarte &amp; Iannuzzi &amp; Grossi" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Costa &amp; Duarte &amp; Iannuzzi &amp; Grossi" baseAuthorityYear="1977" box="[537,683,556,581]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Strategus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="221" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="waldenfelsi">
<emphasis box="[537,683,556,581]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="221">P. waldenfelsi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the smooth pronotal concavity in male and female with tergite VIII weakly convex in lateral view (
<bibRefCitation author="Dupuis F" box="[839,984,591,616]" pageId="31" pageNumber="221" pagination="179 - 184" refId="ref13276" refString="Dupuis F. 2019. Gibboryctes impunctatus, nouvelle espece du Perou (Coleoptera, Dynastidae). Coleopteres. 25: 179 - 184." type="journal article" year="2019">Dupuis 2019</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ratcliffe BC &amp; Cave RD &amp; Paucar-Cabrera A" pageId="31" pageNumber="221" pagination="1 - 586" refId="ref13968" refString="Ratcliffe BC, Cave RD, Paucar-Cabrera A. 2020. The dynastine scarab beetle of Ecuador. Bull Univ Nebraska State Mus. 32: 1 - 586." type="journal article" year="2020">Ratcliffe et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[160,902,710,771]" box="[160,642,710,736]" pageId="31" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,642,710,736]" pageId="31" pageNumber="221">
Geographical distribution (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[490,642,710,736]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="221">
<figureCitation box="[490,598,710,736]" captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="17.[160,227,1388,1411]" captionTargetBox="[168,1147,145,1355]" captionTargetId="figure-89@17.[166,1149,142,1357]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="Figure 14. Geographic distribution maps. (a) Tetragus species; (b) Gibboryctes species; (c) Heterogomphus gracilicornis Prell." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758347" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758347/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="221">Figure 14</figureCitation>
(a))
</emphasis>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[160,902,710,771]" box="[160,902,746,771]" pageId="31" pageNumber="221">
Known from 
<collectingCountry box="[307,358,746,771]" name="Peru" pageId="31" pageNumber="221">Peru</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[415,506,746,771]" name="Ecuador" pageId="31" pageNumber="221">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Dupuis F" box="[520,663,746,771]" pageId="31" pageNumber="221" pagination="179 - 184" refId="ref13276" refString="Dupuis F. 2019. Gibboryctes impunctatus, nouvelle espece du Perou (Coleoptera, Dynastidae). Coleopteres. 25: 179 - 184." type="journal article" year="2019">Dupuis 2019</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ratcliffe BC &amp; Cave RD &amp; Paucar-Cabrera A" box="[676,889,746,771]" pageId="31" pageNumber="221" pagination="1 - 586" refId="ref13968" refString="Ratcliffe BC, Cave RD, Paucar-Cabrera A. 2020. The dynastine scarab beetle of Ecuador. Bull Univ Nebraska State Mus. 32: 1 - 586." type="journal article" year="2020">Ratcliffe et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="221" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="31.[160,1155,830,960]" box="[160,262,830,856]" pageId="31" pageNumber="221">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,262,830,856]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="221">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[160,1155,830,960]" pageId="31" pageNumber="221">
This species was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Dupuis F" box="[511,669,866,891]" pageId="31" pageNumber="221" pagination="179 - 184" refId="ref13276" refString="Dupuis F. 2019. Gibboryctes impunctatus, nouvelle espece du Perou (Coleoptera, Dynastidae). Coleopteres. 25: 179 - 184." type="journal article" year="2019">Dupuis (2019)</bibRefCitation>
and subsequently redescribed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ratcliffe BC &amp; Cave RD &amp; Paucar-Cabrera A" pageId="31" pageNumber="221" pagination="1 - 586" refId="ref13968" refString="Ratcliffe BC, Cave RD, Paucar-Cabrera A. 2020. The dynastine scarab beetle of Ecuador. Bull Univ Nebraska State Mus. 32: 1 - 586." type="journal article" year="2020">Ratcliffe et al. (2020)</bibRefCitation>
concomitantly to our revision of 
<taxonomicName box="[694,821,900,925]" class="Insecta" family="Dynastidae" genus="Gibboryctes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="221" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[694,821,900,925]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="221">Gibboryctes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. For this reason, the species description was not included in this revision.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
